This paper is about federated learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on neural architecture search in federated learning, which involves optimizing the architecture of neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision), which are also related to machine learning. The paper also involves computational and communication costs, which suggests categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
